# Mongoose Coding Standards
- For UUIDs, always use `type: String` with a comment `// UUID`. Do not use `Types.UUID`.
- For Decimals, always use `type: mongoose.Schema.Types.Decimal128`.
- Always use `{ timestamps: true }` instead of manually defining createdAt/updatedAt.
- When instantiating an ObjectId, you MUST use the `new` keyword (e.g., `new mongoose.Types.ObjectId()`). Do not call it as a function.
- When defining a Mongoose Schema, avoid `type: Object`. Define the strict interface or use `Schema.Types.Mixed`.